Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @Zucchini{1%unit} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @Button Mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Halve @Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}. Mince @Chives{1/4%ounce}. Quarter @Lemon{1%unit}.

Pat @Scallops{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously all over with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add zucchini; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and softened, ~{4-6%minutes}. Transfer to a #medium bowl{}.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for zucchini over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}. Turn off heat; season with salt and pepper, then transfer to bowl with zucchini. Wash out pan.

Once water is boiling, add @Penne Pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

While penne cooks, heat @Butter{1/2%tablespoon} (1 TBSP for 4 servings) and a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for mushrooms over medium-high heat. Add tomatoes and season with @Italian Seasoning{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4), salt, and pepper. (Use the rest of the Italian Seasoning as you like.) Cook, stirring, until tomatoes are softened, ~{2-4%minutes}. Stir in half the chives and juice from half the lemon.

Reduce heat to low, then stir in @Mushroom Stock Concentrate{1%unit} and ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water (1⁄3 cup for 4). Whisk in @Crème Fraîche{4%tablespoon}; season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, heat @Butter{1%tablespoon} and a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a medium, preferably nonstick, pan over high heat. Once pan is very hot, add scallops; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Add zucchini, mushrooms, and drained penne to pan with sauce; stir to combine. Stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until melted.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between bowls. Sprinkle with @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup} and remaining chives. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

Serve scallops atop pasta.